gn=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=daak>Daak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/02 2:29:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> According to the new patch information, Dex, to a rogue, will improve defensive skills.<br><br>What is a &quot;defensive skill&quot;? Is it parry, shield block, evade? If it is, then, a rogue only has one of these skills, meaning, that our primary stat only makes us better in Evading? Of course this can be a good thing.<br><br>Or is defensive skill, ArmroFactor? Meaning our higher Dex, will increase our Armor Factor's, making Mob's, in theory, miss more or hit for less?<br><br>Does it make more sense for Quickness to be out primary, as it would allow us quicker attacks, something, that would be unique to Rogue type?<br><br>I haven't tried the new patch much, but right now my Dex is 140, and my Quickness is something like 90. I'm just wondering if swapping the two would be better.<br><br>Of course, I don't know what a &quot;defensive skill&quot; is. <p>====<BR><img src="http://nightmare.madeats.com/daak.jpg"><BR>"Daak is baak let's attaak" (<A HREF="http://nightmare.madeats.com/daak.gif">Shibby</a>!)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeryath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keryath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/02 4:20:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stat meanings</span><hr size=1> Advice: Before trying to get Mythic to pony up info about stats, spend a week screaming at a rock.<br><br>I still can't even get them to explain what <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> exactly</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> absorb does. =( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 5:26:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stat meanings</span><hr size=1> More quickness equalls weaker hits.<br><br>Just something to keep in mind. <br><br>-Anni <p>A.K.A.MoonflowerNightshade/SeamstressHibernia-Guinivere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uneeily.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neeily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 7:08:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> Dex helps us cast faster <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>And yes, as Anni says, quick makes us swing for less damage...but they forgot to mention that we swing far more often. <p>Neeily Loddenfot <BR>Scout of Loki <BR><BR><BR>"I came here to kick butt and chew gum, and I am all out of gum...oh, wait, i have a piece left.  Nevermind :)"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphaelondaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaelon DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 7:08:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stat meanings</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  More quickness equalls weaker hits.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I was going to start a new post about this, but maybe I'll just throw this in here.<br><br>After yesterdays patch, I log on, go out with my buddy to hunt imps, torcs and whatever else is near in the Gorge.  I get the full compliment of druid buffs.  Head out to grab something to kill.  I pull it back to the camp and what do I see.<br><br>You miss.<br>You miss.<br>You miss.<br>You hit for 23 points of damage.<br>You miss.<br>You miss.<br><br>Im thinking, what the hell is going on here?  I never miss like this!  On top of that, my best hit was 32!!  Yes, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  32</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->!!  Day before the patch, I was rarely missing and hitting in the upper 40's.  So Im thinking it has something to do with the buffs.  I drop haste and quickness.  I start hitting a little better, slower obviously, but still not as good as I was.  I then drop the dex buff and what do we have here?  Im back to hitting for what I was prepatch.  A tad slower, but I'll take slower upper 40's over faster misses any day of the week.  Im going to mess around with it some more tonight and see if dropping quick/dex even more will up my damage.  <br><br>I talked to a Nightshade friend about it last night and he was missing a lot more too.  He does the same thing I do, pairs up with a druid and goes out to kill reds and low purples.  Told him to try the same thing, drop some buffs, but I had to log before he got a chance to test it out.<br><br>Anyone else notice this yesterday?<br>[EDIT]<br>Just thought about this.  I leveled the night before the patch.  Went, trained CS up to 29, got Leaper, but didnt train anything else.  My weapon skill dropped off to around 77% of my level whereas it was 81% before I leveled.  Im going to go throw a point on it and see if my damage output ups any.  I'll try hunting without training first, log it all, see what buffs I have on, do all the tests I can, to figure out what could have possibly dropped my damage like that.<br>Phaelon Ocius<br>32nd Season Nightshade<br>Divine Wind - Percival <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphaelondaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaelon DAoC</A> at: 1/30/02 7:20:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=daak>Daak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 6:41:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stat meanings</span><hr size=1> Dex doesn't help, me as an Inflitrator cast faster :P <br><br>While it makes me sad, if its true that more quickness, and maybe even more dex makes you hit for less, but faster, it makes sense Mythic would overlook this. Just because someone is quicker doesnt make them weak, its nonsense.<br><br>I still don't know what a &quot;defensive skill&quot; is.. <br><br>Hello ROCK...<br>SCREAM-&gt;ROCK<br><br>No response. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=daak>Daak</A> at: 1/30/02 6:43:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usirsameth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirSameth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 8:26:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> I have about 160dex now, so this had better not be true...I will also try taking off all my dex gear and see how I perform.<br><br>Btw, was it Mythic that said dex for rogues is defensive? That's pure BS if it's true because that's our main stat that gets raised, and we are supposed to be assassins, not tanks...I get killed as fast as casters with or without a few more hundredreths of a percent of a chance to evade. By defensive &quot;skill&quot; I am guessing that they do mean parry/block/evade, which translates to just evade for most assassins.<br><br>Maybe this is to make even for all the +stat buffs that were recently added to items..<br><br>Sameth<br>30th Infiltrator <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeryath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keryath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerface.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 10:56:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> As far as the missing goes, the rumblings are that red con weapons pretty much suck to use now. Not only do you ruin them faster, now people are starting to think that after this last patch you have less of a chance to hit. I haven't tested this myself so I can't verify it's true. However, if that is a red weapon you are using and seeing large miss rates, pull out an orange or yellow con and see if it gets better.<br><br>Oh, and the theory that quickness reduces damage is only partly correct. You <b>do</b> see a small decrease, but your damage over time is still improved. As far as to what exactly causes this I can't say, but that 'DPS is a constant' rumor is just that, a rumor. <p><img=http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerysmall2.jpg></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeryath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keryath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerface.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/30/02 11:05:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 2:03:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> I'm finding the deep purple items I'm using are not getting damaged as often since the patch.  In six bubbles of fighting and taking a good share of hits, nothing got damaged. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukrugkopf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krugkopf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 3:40:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> Hmm...since the latest patch I've evaded and been missed more often.<br><br>Against a low blue shrieking willow, I evade twice out of three attacks.  Against a low yellow shrieking willow, I evade once out of four attacks.  This does not include outright misses.<br><br>(Using a dwarven cleaver at level 22, I kill them in all in two or three hits, so four attacks is the most they ever get on me.)<br> <p><i>"People will believe any lie you give them; whether it is because they wish it to be true, or fear it to be true." -<b>Wizard's First Rule</i></b><Br><Br><b>Mundus Vult Decipi</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphaelondaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaelon DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 8:19:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> ok, just a quick update.  Went out with a group to the Mines in Hibernia, Crosucating or whatever.  We had 2 druids in the group, so I was pestering them to help me test what buffs did what.  <br><br>At first I told them to just give me Str, dex and con buffs.  I was attacking at my usual rate and hitting on high reds for 35+ with very few misses.  So I ask for haste.  We go through about 20 or so mobs and Im doing between 30-35 damage a lot faster.  So then I ask for the quickness buff.  Bufss my quick up to about 160 or something from 123.  Miss, Miss, Miss, you hit for 29, Miss....you get the idea.  I tried it on 3-4 mobs and had to get rid of it.  The damage output for the group was killing our healers.  I wont be asking for quick buffs from anyone anymore.  Might even stay away from haste because all that did was draw agro on me.  Dex, Str, and a con buff please.  Keeps my damage up and agro off me.  <br><br>Also, with 210 dex or somewhere around there, I was evading high reds low purples like it was going out of style.  I think I got hit a total of 3 times out of maybe 20 swings in the hour and a half we were in there.<br><br>Going to go off and do some solo testing with druid buffs tonight.  I'll be sure to log everything so I have better data for everyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=daak>Daak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 12:44:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Btw, was it Mythic that said dex for rogues is defensive? That's pure BS if it's true because that's our main stat that gets raised, and we are supposed to be assassins, not tanks...I get killed as fast as casters with or without a few more hundredreths of a percent of a chance to evade. By defensive &quot;skill&quot; I am guessing that they do mean parry/block/evade, which translates to just evade for most assassins.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>This is my axact reason for starting the Thread... <br><br>It's really a double-edged sword here, on the one hand we Evade a heck of a lot more, according to Phaelon, while this helps when we draw agro which happens, it doesn't help in the long run.<br><br>BTW, anyone try using a Shield lately and seeing how often you Shield Block? Just a though.<br><br>It'd be nice if we could get a clearer definition on how STR/DEX effect weapon types... I still can't except the whole 50/50 for thrusting.<br><br>But, what else are you going to make DEX primarily affect? It only makes sense that it effects &quot;defense&quot;, because what else could it effect <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphaelondaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaelon DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 5:08:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why is primary stat Dex for Rogue types? Good and Bad</span><hr size=1> Small Sample here, 3 mobs unbuffed, 5 str/con buffed, then another 5 with the works Dex, Quick, Haste, Str, Con...whatever else a level 34 druid might have.<br><br>Unbuffed (147dex, 133qui)<br><br>Average Style Damage per Mob<br>bonus ( to hit percentage ) [ success percentage ]<br><br>Leaper  +23.0 (100.0%/1) [50.0%]<br>Achilles Heel +22.8 (90.0%/10) [47.4%]<br>Garrote +14.9 (100.0%/12) [50.0%]<br>Hamstring  +10.0 (100.0%/1) [50.0%]<br>Diamondback +20.0 (50.0%/2) [20.0%]<br>Perforate Artery +144.7 (100.0%/3) [50.0%]<br>_______________________________________________<br>Average Damage D