g.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That's bad.  That means your defense is worse (which, in context, makes sense).<br><br>From the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotherald.com/more/185.php">Camelot Herald</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->: &quot;Short version – the checks are hit/miss, evade, parry, block.&quot;  The first check is hit or miss.  If you're evading more, you're getting missed less.  Since your chance to evade should remain more or less the same - and certainly shouldn't go down with a higher dex - you should be taking more hits than you would have before.<br><br>Of course, with the higher Constitution, that's not likely a problem. <p><b>Ciardha Sidhe</b>, Elven Nightshade of Guinevere<br><small>Explorer 93% | Killer 60% | Socializer 40% | Achiever 6%</small><br>&quot;You killed a little dwarf.  You brute.&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskyro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skyro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/02 3:10:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1950.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> uh...</span><hr size=1> what? It says it checks if it's a hit/miss first before evade. That means you only evade if it was going to be a hit. More dex means you evade more which is good no matter how you look at it. Of course if you're comparing what would do a sb more good, it would probably be str. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uciardhasidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ciardha Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/02 4:05:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.c